</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dPZUdm cBqcmb pf-24_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-25_ pf-text-1">40% of accidents in nurseries are due to slips, trips, and falls (HSE).



</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-27_ pf-text-1">The EYFS framework mandates a safe and suitable environment for children.



</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-29_ pf-text-1"><em><strong><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/childcare-and-early-years-courses-training" target="_blank"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span></a></strong></em>Providers must comply with the Health and Safety at Work Act 1974 and the Childcare Act 2006.



</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-jXbVAB kNtuek pf-31_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bDoQz cmNGeH pf-32_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-33_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dPZUdm cBqcmb pf-35_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-36_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health and safety </strong>- Measures and practices in place to prevent accidents, injuries, and illnesses within a childcare setting.




</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-38_ pf-text-1"><strong>Risk assessment</strong> - A systematic process of evaluating potential risks that could be involved in a projected activity or undertaking.




</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-40_ pf-text-1"><strong>Safeguarding</strong> - Protecting children from harm, abuse, and neglect while ensuring their development and well-being.





</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-jXbVAB kNtuek pf-42_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bDoQz cmNGeH pf-43_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-44_ pf-heading-1-h3">Legislation and regulations
</h3><p class="sc-kAkozD iOjmJ pf-46_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Childcare providers must adhere to several key pieces of legislation and regulations:



</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dPZUdm cBqcmb pf-48_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-49_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health and Safety at Work Act 1974</strong> - Requires employers to ensure the health, safety, and welfare of employees and non-employees.





</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-51_ pf-text-1"><strong>Childcare Act 2006</strong> - Sets the standards for early years provision and ensures that children's welfare is paramount.




</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-53_ pf-text-1"><strong>EYFS Framework </strong>- Provides statutory guidelines for all early years providers, covering health and safety requirements.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-jXbVAB kNtuek pf-55_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bDoQz cmNGeH pf-56_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-57_ pf-heading-1-h3">Best practices for implementation
</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-59_ pf-heading-1-h3">Conducting regular risk assessments
</h3><p class="sc-kAkozD iOjmJ pf-61_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Conducting thorough risk assessments is crucial. Identify potential hazards, assess the risks associated with them, and implement control measures to mitigate these risks. Regularly review and update risk assessments to reflect any changes in the environment or activities.



</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-63_ pf-heading-1-h3">Training and professional development
</h3><p class="sc-kAkozD iOjmJ pf-65_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Ensure all staff are adequately trained in health and safety procedures. This includes first aid training, fire safety, and safe handling of materials. Continuing professional development (CPD) is vital to keep staff updated on the latest safety practices and regulatory changes.
<br><br><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/childcare-and-early-years-courses-training" target="_blank"><em><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);">Click here to stay on top of your professional development with our childcare and early years online training courses</span></em></a>.
</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-67_ pf-heading-1-h3">Maintaining a safe environment
</h3><p class="sc-kAkozD iOjmJ pf-69_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Regular maintenance and inspection of the premises are essential. Ensure that play equipment is safe and suitable for children's ages and abilities. Implement clear policies for managing accidents and incidents, including detailed reporting and follow-up procedures.





</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-71_ pf-heading-1-h3">Health and hygiene practices
</h3><p class="sc-kAkozD iOjmJ pf-73_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Promote good hygiene practices to prevent the spread of illnesses. This includes regular handwashing, cleaning and sanitising surfaces, and ensuring proper food hygiene. Establish protocols for dealing with illnesses and infectious diseases, including exclusion periods and notification procedures.






</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jXbVAB kNtuek pf-75_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bDoQz cmNGeH pf-76_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-77_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommendations</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dPZUdm cBqcmb pf-79_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-80_ pf-text-1"><strong>Adopt a proactive approach</strong> - Regularly review and update health and safety policies and procedures.








</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-82_ pf-text-1"><strong>Engage staff in training</strong> -&nbsp;Provide ongoing CPD opportunities for staff to stay current with health and safety practices.






</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-84_ pf-text-1"><strong>Utilise technology</strong> - Implement compliance management software like ComplyPlus™ to streamline the management of health and safety requirements and ensure regulatory compliance.




</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-jXbVAB kNtuek pf-86_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bDoQz cmNGeH pf-87_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-88_ pf-heading-1-h3">Conclusion
